Definitely check out Chinatown neighborhood whenever you’re visiting San Francisco or around Union Square. FYI It’s only 5 mins walk from Union Square 🥰

A Memorable Tea Ceremony in Kyoto: Embracing Japanese Tradition 🍵✨

I had the most amazing time experiencing a traditional tea ceremony in beautiful Kyoto. It was a truly special moment that allowed me to connect with the heart of Japanese culture. 🏯🌸

The tea ceremony is a treasured tradition that emphasizes grace, harmony, and respect. As a guest, I felt warmly welcomed into a peaceful tearoom adorned with lovely decorations. The atmosphere was so calm and soothing. 

Sitting on a soft tatami mat, I watched in awe as the tea master carefully prepared matcha, a powdered green tea. Every movement had a purpose and was done with great care. 🍵❤️🌿

The tea master then handed me a bowl of frothy matcha, its vibrant green color reflecting the beauty of nature. With both hands, I accepted the bowl, feeling a deep connection to centuries of tradition. I took a sip of the tea, and its earthy flavor and comforting warmth filled me with a sense of peace. 

This tea ceremony was more than just a ritual. It was a chance to experience Japanese hospitality, to appreciate the harmony between people and nature, and to find inner tranquility. The memories of this experience will stay with me forever, reminding me of the beauty in simplicity and the power of genuine connections. 🌟🍵❤️

#teaceremony #japanesetraditions #kyotoexperience #mindfulness #matchamagic #culturaljourney

I had the privilege of watching the opera performance called ‘Omar’ at the War Memorial Opera House in San Francisco, and it was truly jaw-dropping to witness Arabic script in it. 

It is a beautiful production based on a true story about an enslaved Muslim from Senegal and his struggles in the US to figure out his identity.

The fusion of opera and the remembrance of Allah was absolutely amazing. This performance moved me in so many ways, showcasing Islam in a powerful light and setting. It was truly inspiring and uplifting, especially during these challenging times. I highly encourage you all to watch ‘Omar.’

📍War Memorial Opera House In San Francisco 
🗓️ November 5th to 21st, 2023.

As a devoted fan of Mediterranean cuisine, I was pleasantly surprised by an exceptional dining experience at @taksimsf . The chef’s attentiveness, coupled with the stunning ambiance, and flawlessly flavorful, artfully presented dishes, surpassed my expectations. I enjoyed this delightful experience with my parents, and Taksim proves to be an ideal choice for both intimate solo dinners and larger gatherings.

Today, San Francisco stood on the right side of history by passing the resolution for a ceasefire!
I’m crying rn 😭😭😭 so happy Shukar Alhumdulilah @deanprestond5 and @hillary.ronen you guys are real heroes!!

Today, San Francisco passed the resolution for a ceasefire in Gaza. Sharing snippets of what happened inside the chambers - there were 200 attendees, 11 board of supervisors from each district. My district supervisor @deanprestond5 (District 5) and @hillary.ronen (District 9) sponsored the resolution calling for a sustained ceasefire in Gaza and providing humanitarian aid. 

It was a rewarding experience to witness the entire resolution process, listen to each supervisor, and ultimately see 8 supervisors vote ‘YES’ towards the resolution.

Today, San Francisco stood on the right side of history, and I’m so glad I got to witness it with @sobiaitwaru . This is just the beginning 🤍🤍 #everyvoicematters #sanfrancisco #resolutionpassed
